{{Wireless embedded system |brand=Netgear |model=EX3110 |fcc_date=07/26/2017 |manuf_country=China |is_manuf=No |type=range extender |fcc_id=PY317100370 |pwr_v=100-240 |pwr_amp=0.15 |pwr_ac_hz=50/60 |wi1_802dot11_protocols=an+ac |wi1_txchains=1 |wi1_rxchains=1 |wi1_sstreams=1 |wi2_802dot11_protocols=bgn |wi2_txchains=2 |wi2_rxchains=2 |wi2_sstreams=2 |flags=DFS (master), DFS (slave), |802dot11_protocols=abgn+ac }} {{TagLine|AC750 WiFi Range Extender}} :{{ProductPage|https://www.netgear.com/home/products/networking/wifi-range-extenders/EX3110.aspx}}{{SupportPage|vendor=Netgear|model=EX3110}}
{{FCC ST|01/22/2018|indexme.}}
Test Report documents on the FCC show that this device is capable of two spatial streams for both 2.4GHz and 5GHz (AC1200) but may be artificially limited to single stream for 5GHz (AC750). Since this device and the [[Netgear EX6110]] both hit the FCC on the same day, they likely use identical hardware.
A [https://fccid.io/PY317100370#Exhibits-3 C2PC FCC filing on 9/14/2017] adds DFS support with firmware version 1.0.0.32. The initial version posted to the Netgear website is [https://kb.netgear.com/000047414/EX3110-EX6110-Firmware-Version-1-0-0-44 1.0.0.44].
